## TOPs OBJ Mesh Sequence to ZIP Archive

### Example HIP: 

* TOPs\_OBJ\_Mesh\_Sequence\_to\_ZIP\_Archive\_V001.hip

### Description:

Create a zip archive that backs up the Wavefront OBJ/MTL meshes, and UDIM based PNG texture maps:

* $HIP/obj/Mesh.\*.obj  
* $HIP/obj/Mesh.\*.mtl  
* $HIP/obj/Mesh\_u\*\_v\*.\*.png

The zip archive is saved to:

* $HIP/zip/Mesh.zip

![][image50]

### TOPs Node Parameters:

We start with adding the Wavefront OBJ meshes to the zip archive:

#### File Pattern Node

Files Type: Files Only  
Pattern: $HIP/obj/Mesh.\*.obj

Outputs:  
\[x\] Output Attribute: filesOBJ  
\[x\] Output File Tag: file/archive

![][image51]

#### Attribute from String Node

Source String:\`@filesOBJ\`  
Operation: Match by Pattern  
Pattern Type: Simple Pattern  
Pattern: {meshName:string}.{seq:string}.obj

![][image52]

#### Range Generate Node

Specify Range As: Value Range  
Value Range: 1-153 ("Right click \> Delete Channels" to unlock the number inputs)  
\[x\] Inclusive  
Store Value as: Custom Attribute  
Attribute Name: rangeValue  
\[x\] Set Range Attribute: range

Note: Set the "End Frame" range value to line up with the number of frames in the image sequence.

![][image53]

#### Wait For All Node

Merge Output Files: All Files  
![][image54]

#### File Compress Node

Source:  
File is to Compress: Custom File Path  
Path: \`@filesOBJ\`  
Output:  
Compression Method: ZIP  
Output File: $HIP/zip/Mesh.zip  
\[x\] Compress Archive  
\[x\] Append to Existing Archive

![][image55]

Then we add the Wavefront Material (.mtl) files to the zip archive:

#### File Pattern Node

Files Type: Files Only  
Pattern: $HIP/obj/Mesh.\*.mtl

Outputs:  
\[x\] Output Attribute: filesMTL  
\[x\] Output File Tag: file/archive

![][image56]

#### Attribute from String Node

Source String:\`@filesOBJ\`

Pattern: {meshName:string}.{seq:string}.mtl

![][image57]

#### Range Generate Node

Specify Range As: Value Range  
Value Range: 1-153 ("Right click \> Delete Channels" to unlock the number inputs)  
\[x\] Inclusive

Attribute Name: rangeValue  
\[x\] Set Range Attribute: range

Note: Set the "End Frame" range value to line up with the number of frames in the image sequence.

![][image58]

#### Wait For All Node

Merge Output Files: All Files  
![][image59]

#### File Compress Node

Source:  
File is to Compress: Custom File Path  
Path: \`@filesMTL\`  
Output:  
Compression Method: ZIP  
Output File: $HIP/zip`/`Mesh.zip  
\[x\] Compress Archive  
\[x\] Append to Existing Archive

![][image60]
